.TH ZOPEN-REMOVE "1" "June 2026" "zopen tools 0.8.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zopen-remove \- manual page for zopen-remove 0.8.5
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zopen-remove
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGE\/\fR] ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-remove is a utility for zopen community to remove an installed package or
packages.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR, \-?
display this help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-purge\fR
remove package, the versioned directory, and any
cached files.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
run in verbose mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
print version.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
automatically answer yes to prompts.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
zopen remove foo bar
interactively remove the foo and bar packages if installed
.TP
zopen remove \-\-yes foo bar
remove the foo and bar packages if installed, without
asking for confirmation
